ux.name: ux
ux.description: The MIB module for Sonus entities. This MIB module describes the enterprise traps for the Sonus SBC 1000 and 2000.

uxAlmADcachingfailed.name: uxAlmADcachingfailed
uxAlmADcachingfailed.description: Failed to cache attributes from AD in memory. Suggested action - try again later. This alarm will be cleared by event AD caching successful.

uxAlmOnlineADqueryfailed.name: uxAlmOnlineADqueryfailed
uxAlmOnlineADqueryfailed.description: Failed to execute AD query. Suggested action - confirm that AD is network reachable, check the AD configuration as well as AD access credentials.

uxAlmUserloggedin.name: uxAlmUserloggedin
uxAlmUserloggedin.description: New user 'username' logged in from 'ip address'.

uxAlmUserloginfailed.name: uxAlmUserloginfailed
uxAlmUserloginfailed.description: User 'username' login failed from 'ip' at 'time'. This alarm will be cleared by event User logged in.

uxAlmADUnreachable.name: uxAlmADUnreachable
uxAlmADUnreachable.description: Either AD is network unreachable, or the AD credentials are invalid. This alarm will be cleared by 'AD Reachable' event.

uxAlmADbackupfailed.name: uxAlmADbackupfailed
uxAlmADbackupfailed.description: Failed to backup cached values from AD to storage device. Either the storage device is not present, or it is full. Contact Sonus TAC for further assistance.

uxAlmADsuccessfullybackedup.name: uxAlmADsuccessfullybackedup
uxAlmADsuccessfullybackedup.description: Successful backup of cached values from AD to storage device.

uxAlmADcachetruncated.name: uxAlmADcachetruncated
uxAlmADcachetruncated.description: AD Cache is truncated, AD cache results have exceeded the maximum cache size. Consider caching only the required attributes. If the query is not found in cache, Online query will be performed, while affecting performance.

uxAlmRADIUSServerUnreachable.name: uxAlmRADIUSServerUnreachable
uxAlmRADIUSServerUnreachable.description: Either the RADIUS server is network unreachable, the configuration is incorrect, or due to service impacting change. Suggested action - check shared secret, listening port, RADIUS server IP. This alarm will be cleared by 'RADIUS Reachable' event.

uxAlmCDRloggingfailed.name: uxAlmCDRloggingfailed
uxAlmCDRloggingfailed.description: Sonus SBC failed to send CDR to RADIUS based accounting server. Either the server is network unreachable, or the configuration is incorrect. Suggested action - check shared secret, listening port, RADIUS server IP.

uxAlmCDRbackupfailed.name: uxAlmCDRbackupfailed
uxAlmCDRbackupfailed.description: Sonus SBC failed to backup CDR in local file. Either running with low disk space or CDR backup maximum limit is crossed. Suggested action - Free up the disk space or save the CDR Queued file for future reference.

uxAlmUserpasswordchangedsuccessfully.name: uxAlmUserpasswordchangedsuccessfully
uxAlmUserpasswordchangedsuccessfully.description: Password changed successfully by 'username' from 'ip address'.

uxAlmUserpasswordchangefailed.name: uxAlmUserpasswordchangefailed
uxAlmUserpasswordchangefailed.description: Password change attempted by 'username' from 'ip address' failed.

uxAlmUseraccountdisabled.name: uxAlmUseraccountdisabled
uxAlmUseraccountdisabled.description: Account has been disabled by 'username' from 'ip address'.

uxAlmUseraccountactivated.name: uxAlmUseraccountactivated
uxAlmUseraccountactivated.description: Account has been activated by 'username' from 'ip address'.

uxAlmUserloginblocked.name: uxAlmUserloginblocked
uxAlmUserloginblocked.description: User attempting to log in from 'ip' blocked due to excessive incorrect login attempts.

uxAlmUserpasswordexpired.name: uxAlmUserpasswordexpired
uxAlmUserpasswordexpired.description: Password has expired. User 'username' logging in from 'ip' password is expired.

uxAlmADMaximumThreadsExceeded.name: uxAlmADMaximumThreadsExceeded
uxAlmADMaximumThreadsExceeded.description: AD has reached maximum threads. Please inform your service representative.

uxAlmADcachingtimedout.name: uxAlmADcachingtimedout
uxAlmADcachingtimedout.description: Timed out caching attributes due to lack of response from AD. Suggested action - try again later. The SBC will attempt to load the last successful cache from backup.

uxAlmInvalidCardIDEEPROMData.name: uxAlmInvalidCardIDEEPROMData
uxAlmInvalidCardIDEEPROMData.description: A Card was detected with invalid Card ID EEPROM contents (failed CRC-CCITT check). Suggested action - provide the entire alarm message including the numbers at the end to Sonus TAC for further assistance.

uxAlmCardHealthCheckFailed.name: uxAlmCardHealthCheckFailed
uxAlmCardHealthCheckFailed.description: During Line Card activation, a Card Fault was detected after power was applied to the card. The Card will remain out-of-service. Suggested action - reboot system. If issue persists, contact Sonus TAC with the alarm information.

uxAlmCardnotSupported.name: uxAlmCardnotSupported
uxAlmCardnotSupported.description: A Card was detected which can be identified, but the Sonus SBC system software is unable to support. The Card will remain out-of-service. Suggested action - reboot system. If issue persists, contact Sonus TAC with the alarm information.

uxAlmPowerSupplyinputfailure.name: uxAlmPowerSupplyinputfailure
uxAlmPowerSupplyinputfailure.description: A Power supply module has indicated a failure of input power. The Sonus SBC System has lost Power Supply redundancy. Suggested action - Verify that the power cable is connected and that the PS is functioning properly.

uxAlmPowerSupplyinputrestored.name: uxAlmPowerSupplyinputrestored
uxAlmPowerSupplyinputrestored.description: A Power Supply module has indicated that input power has been restored. This event clears the 'Power Supply Input Failure' Alarm.

uxAlmPowerSupplyoutputfailure.name: uxAlmPowerSupplyoutputfailure
uxAlmPowerSupplyoutputfailure.description: A Power Supply module has indicated a failure of output power. The Sonus SBC System has lost Power Supply redundancy. Suggested action - Verify that the PS is functioning properly.

uxAlmSingleFanfailure.name: uxAlmSingleFanfailure
uxAlmSingleFanfailure.description: Check the System tab to find the Fan ID of the failed fan. Contact Sonus TAC with this information.

uxAlmMultipleFanFailures.name: uxAlmMultipleFanFailures
uxAlmMultipleFanFailures.description: Check the System tab to find the Fan ID's of the failed fans. Contact Sonus TAC with this information.

uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarm.name: uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarm
uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarm.description: The temperature sensors have indicated that the system is running warm (55 degrees C threshold).

uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarmCleared.name: uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarmCleared
uxAlmSystemTemperatureWarmCleared.description: The temperature sensors have indicated that the system is no longer running warm (55 degrees C threshold). This event clears the 'System Temperature Warm' Alarm.

uxAlmSystemTemperatureHot.name: uxAlmSystemTemperatureHot
uxAlmSystemTemperatureHot.description: The temperature sensors have indicated that system is running hot (65 degrees C threshold).

uxAlmSystemTemperatureHotCleared.name: uxAlmSystemTemperatureHotCleared
uxAlmSystemTemperatureHotCleared.description: The temperature sensors have indicated that the system is no longer running hot (65 degrees C threshold). This event clears the 'System Temperature Hot' Alarm.

uxAlmLicensesexpired.name: uxAlmLicensesexpired
uxAlmLicensesexpired.description: License of the node has expired, all the licensed features would fail to work. Contact Sonus Enterprise Sales.

uxAlmLicenseexpiresin2weeks.name: uxAlmLicenseexpiresin2weeks
uxAlmLicenseexpiresin2weeks.description: License of the node will expire in 2 weeks.

uxAlmNewLicenseapplied.name: uxAlmNewLicenseapplied
uxAlmNewLicenseapplied.description: New License is applied on the node.

uxAlmFailedtoApplyLicense.name: uxAlmFailedtoApplyLicense
uxAlmFailedtoApplyLicense.description: Either an invalid key is used, or the license key applies to a different node, or the license key expiry is past the present date. Contact Sonus Sales to obtain a new license.

uxAlmFailedtoacquirelicense.name: uxAlmFailedtoacquirelicense
uxAlmFailedtoacquirelicense.description: License(s) for TDM/SIP/SBA/Transcoding/AD have exhausted or TDM/SIP/SBA/Transcoding/AD is not licensed.

uxAlmLicensedDS1portsexceedsinstalledpor.name: uxAlmLicensedDS1portsexceedsinstalledports
uxAlmLicensedDS1portsexceedsinstalledpor.description: The alarm is generated when the license key applied has more DS1 ports licensed than are installed in the system. The number of BRI ports installed will get activated. As a fix, obtain a license with correct number of DS1 ports.

uxAlmLicensedBRIportsexceedsinstalledpor.name: uxAlmLicensedBRIportsexceedsinstalledports
uxAlmLicensedBRIportsexceedsinstalledpor.description: The alarm is generated when the license key applied has more BRI ports licensed than are installed in the system. The number of BRI ports installed will get activated. As a fix, obtain a license with correct number of BRI ports.

uxAlmLicensedFXSportsexceedsinstalledpor.name: uxAlmLicensedFXSportsexceedsinstalledports
uxAlmLicensedFXSportsexceedsinstalledpor.description: The alarm is generated when the license key applied has more FXS ports licensed than are installed in the system. The number of FXS ports installed will get activated. As a fix, obtain a license with correct number of FXS ports.

uxAlmLicensedFXOportsexceedsinstalledpor.name: uxAlmLicensedFXOportsexceedsinstalledports
uxAlmLicensedFXOportsexceedsinstalledpor.description: The alarm is generated when the license key applied has more FXO ports licensed than are installed in the system. The number of FXO ports installed will get activated. As a fix, obtain a license with correct number of FXO ports.

uxAlmASMUnreachable.name: uxAlmASMUnreachable
uxAlmASMUnreachable.description: ASM system can not be reached, system is down. Check whether the ASM is rebooting.

uxAlmASMFailureRecovered.name: uxAlmASMFailureRecovered
uxAlmASMFailureRecovered.description: ASM system was previously unreachable, but has come up. This alarm doesn't autoclear so the user can investigate the cause, but the system should be working correctly now.

uxAlmASMServicesNotRunning.name: uxAlmASMServicesNotRunning
uxAlmASMServicesNotRunning.description: ASM services are not running, calls through the ASM cannot be placed.

uxAlmASMServicesRestarted.name: uxAlmASMServicesRestarted
uxAlmASMServicesRestarted.description: ASM Services was previously stopped, but has started. This alarm doesn't autoclear so the user can investigate the cause, but ASM Services should be working correctly now.

uxAlmASMServiceRestartFailed.name: uxAlmASMServiceRestartFailed
uxAlmASMServiceRestartFailed.description: The system attempted to restart a failed service on the ASM, service did not start successfully. User interaction is required.

uxAlmASMSystemStarted.name: uxAlmASMSystemStarted
uxAlmASMSystemStarted.description: This event is set when the SBA communication system is first established, and usually indicates that the Application Solution Module (ASM) has finished booting. It should come up at system startup, it may come again if the ASM hardware is rebooted.

uxAlmASMSystemShuttingdown.name: uxAlmASMSystemShuttingdown
uxAlmASMSystemShuttingdown.description: A planned or deliberate shut down is taking place on the Application Solution Module (ASM).

uxAlmEthernetLinkDown.name: uxAlmEthernetLinkDown
uxAlmEthernetLinkDown.description: Ethernet port specified has lost link. Source Instance: Eth0/Eth1 via SBA Monitor.

uxAlmEthernetLinkUp.name: uxAlmEthernetLinkUp
uxAlmEthernetLinkUp.description: Ethernet port specific has recovered link.

uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMismatch.name: uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMismatch
uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMismatch.description: The ASM and Sonus SBC IP interfaces are in different subnets and cannot communicate.

uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMatch.name: uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMatch
uxAlmASMSBCIPSubnetMatch.description: The ASM and Sonus SBC IP interfaces are in the same subnet and can now communicate.

uxAlmASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable.name: uxAlmASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable
uxAlmASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable.description: The QoE database is unreachable from ASM, make sure the Lync Server 2013 is deployed and Monitoring database is running

uxAlmClearASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable.name: uxAlmClearASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable
uxAlmClearASMQoESQLdatabaseisunreachable.description: The QoE database is now reachable from ASM.

uxAlmASMfailedtostoreQoEinformation.name: uxAlmASMfailedtostoreQoEinformation
uxAlmASMfailedtostoreQoEinformation.description: Failed to store the QoE information from ASM.

uxAlmASMSBCCACUpdatefailed.name: uxAlmASMSBCCACUpdatefailed
uxAlmASMSBCCACUpdatefailed.description: The ASM hasn't been able to apply the CAC update.

uxAlmThiscopyofASMOperatingSystemisnotge.name: uxAlmThiscopyofASMOperatingSystemisnotgenuine
uxAlmThiscopyofASMOperatingSystemisnotge.description: ASM Windows Server is not able to activate as genuine Microsoft product.

uxAlmASMdriveNFSmountfailure.name: uxAlmASMdriveNFSmountfailure
uxAlmASMdriveNFSmountfailure.description: NFS mounting of ASM drive failed, make sure ASM module is up and NFS service is running on the ASM module

uxAlmClearASMdriveNFSmountfailure.name: uxAlmClearASMdriveNFSmountfailure
uxAlmClearASMdriveNFSmountfailure.description: ASM hard drive is NFS mounted and available.

uxAlmASMOperatingSystemSuccessfullyActiv.name: uxAlmASMOperatingSystemSuccessfullyActivated
uxAlmASMOperatingSystemSuccessfullyActiv.description: ASM Windows Server is activate as genuine Microsoft product.

uxAlmConfigurationchangeoccurredonNormal.name: uxAlmConfigurationchangeoccurredonNormalizationTable
uxAlmConfigurationchangeoccurredonNormal.description: There is a normalization table number/name that should be printed with this event.

uxAlmRoutetemporarilydisabled.name: uxAlmRoutetemporarilydisabled
uxAlmRoutetemporarilydisabled.description: Route temporarily disabled due to signaling group(s) down.

uxAlmRouteenabled.name: uxAlmRouteenabled
uxAlmRouteenabled.description: Route enabled as the signaling group is up.

uxAlmACallexceededthelimitfornumberofdes.name: uxAlmACallexceededthelimitfornumberofdestinations
uxAlmACallexceededthelimitfornumberofdes.description: Maximum(8) call forks exceeded, no more forks for this destination

uxAlmCallforkingusedwithnoforkinglicense.name: uxAlmCallforkingusedwithnoforkinglicense
uxAlmCallforkingusedwithnoforkinglicense.description: Call forking used with no forking license.

uxAlmChannelisinservice.name: uxAlmChannelisinservice
uxAlmChannelisinservice.description: Channel is up and is in service. This clears the 'Channel out of service' alarm.

uxAlmChannelisoutofservice.name: uxAlmChannelisoutofservice
uxAlmChannelisoutofservice.description: Channel Out Of Service Alarm. This alarm is automatically cleared when Channel is in service.

uxAlmEmergencyCallAttempted.name: uxAlmEmergencyCallAttempted
uxAlmEmergencyCallAttempted.description: Emergency Call is Attempted from Calling Number, Calling Extension, Caller IP address.

uxAlmEmergencyCallCompleted.name: uxAlmEmergencyCallCompleted
uxAlmEmergencyCallCompleted.description: Emergency Call Alarm will be cleared after expiry time in emergency status table.

uxAlmQoEReportNotSentDuetoRTCPMediaList.name: uxAlmQoEReportNotSentDuetoRTCPMediaList
uxAlmQoEReportNotSentDuetoRTCPMediaList.description: QoE Report for the Signaling Group not sent. To enable QoE report for this Signaling Group, check the Media List associated with the SG and set RTCP Mode to RTCP-XR.

uxAlmCallTransferfailedduetocallnotbeing.name: uxAlmCallTransferfailedduetocallnotbeinginDSPmode
uxAlmCallTransferfailedduetocallnotbeing.description: The call is not in DSP mode - hence the call transfer could not be honored.

uxAlmCallAttemptfailedduetoMediaModemism.name: uxAlmCallAttemptfailedduetoMediaModemismatch
uxAlmCallAttemptfailedduetoMediaModemism.description: The call failed due to Media Mode mismatch across SG and Call Route configuration.

uxAlmSGDrained.name: uxAlmSGDrained
uxAlmSGDrained.description: SG 'rowID' set to Drain Mode, all channels are idle

uxAlmSIPServerNotResponding.name: uxAlmSIPServerNotResponding
uxAlmSIPServerNotResponding.description: SIP server has failed to respond and has been taken out of service. This alarm will be cleared by the event 'SIP server became responsive'.

uxAlmSignalingGroupTakenoutofService.name: uxAlmSignalingGroupTakenoutofService
uxAlmSignalingGroupTakenoutofService.description: All servers in SG have failed. This alarm will be cleared by 'SIP Signaling group enabled' event.

uxAlmSignalingGroupDisabled.name: uxAlmSignalingGroupDisabled
uxAlmSignalingGroupDisabled.description: Configuration action has changed this Signaling Group from Enabled to Disabled.

uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailure.name: uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailure
uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailure.description: TLS server handshake failed with alert code. Action: Refer to Error Alerts in RFC 5246 for the problem.

uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutFai.name: uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutFailure
uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutFai.description: Handshake failed due to no response from peer within specified timeout. Action: Increase the Handshake Inactivity Timeout in TLS Profile.

uxAlmConfiguredPortNumberMismatch.name: uxAlmConfiguredPortNumberMismatch
uxAlmConfiguredPortNumberMismatch.description: Discrepancy of an FQDN/Port configured in the SipServer object that is different than the DNS SRV lookup. A DNS SRV record can return the port number for the selected protocol. The DNS SRV port value will take priority over the configured port.

uxAlmSIPclusterwentdown.name: uxAlmSIPclusterwentdown
uxAlmSIPclusterwentdown.description: SIP cluster went down. This is due to all the servers in the clusters being unresponsive. This alarm will be cleared by the event 'SIP Cluster Enabled'.

uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupDNSFailure.name: uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupDNSFailure
uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupDNSFailure.description: Failed to resolve the FQDN entries in the SIP Signaling Group. Suggested action - confirm the FQDNs, and confirm DNS access.

uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupFQDNResolved.name: uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupFQDNResolved
uxAlmSIPSignalingGroupFQDNResolved.description: Successfully resolved the FQDN of the SIP Signaling group.

uxAlmSIPServerDNSFailure.name: uxAlmSIPServerDNSFailure
uxAlmSIPServerDNSFailure.description: Failed to resolve the SIP server FQDN entries in the SIP Server table. Suggested action - check the FQDN syntax.

uxAlmSIPCallSessionDNSFailure.name: uxAlmSIPCallSessionDNSFailure
uxAlmSIPCallSessionDNSFailure.description: Failed to resolve an FQDN with DNS server during a SIP call session.

uxAlmAcquiringLicenseforRegisterFailed.name: uxAlmAcquiringLicenseforRegisterFailed
uxAlmAcquiringLicenseforRegisterFailed.description: Failed to acquire license from License Manager

uxAlmSessionorOtherResourceLeak.name: uxAlmSessionorOtherResourceLeak
uxAlmSessionorOtherResourceLeak.description: SIP performs self-check for leaks. Please enable logging for sip and issue 'show resources' command.

uxAlmFailedtoBindtoNetworkInterface.name: uxAlmFailedtoBindtoNetworkInterface
uxAlmFailedtoBindtoNetworkInterface.description: Failed to bind to network interface due to dynamic IP address not available.

uxAlmSuccessfullyBoundtoNetworkInterface.name: uxAlmSuccessfullyBoundtoNetworkInterface
uxAlmSuccessfullyBoundtoNetworkInterface.description: Successfully bound to network interface. DHCP lease renewed.

uxAlmSIPRegisterServerNotResponding.name: uxAlmSIPRegisterServerNotResponding
uxAlmSIPRegisterServerNotResponding.description: SIP Register server has failed to respond. This alarm will be cleared by the event 'SIP Register server became responsive'.

uxAlmRegistrationNotValidReceivedstalefa.name: uxAlmRegistrationNotValidReceivedstalefalse
uxAlmRegistrationNotValidReceivedstalefa.description: Stale=false/Registration no longer valid due to Incorrect Credentials.

uxAlmConfigChangeforSIPEndpointThatRecei.name: uxAlmConfigChangeforSIPEndpointThatReceivedstalefalse
uxAlmConfigChangeforSIPEndpointThatRecei.description: Config has changed, clear StaleIsFalse Alarm.

uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasNotSucce.name: uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasNotSuccessful
uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasNotSucce.description: QoE Notify Message received a no response or a failed response. This alarm will be cleared by the event 'QoE Notify Message received a successful response'.

uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasSuccessf.name: uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasSuccessful
uxAlmQoENotifyMessageResponseWasSuccessf.description: QoE Notify Message received a successful response.

uxAlmSystemOverloadCleared.name: uxAlmSystemOverloadCleared
uxAlmSystemOverloadCleared.description: System processing resumes normal operation, overload cleared

uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsReached.name: uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsReached
uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsReached.description: The maximum number of SIP sessions (calls/register/subscribe) has been reached on the signaling group. Increase the number of SIP Channels for the signaling group.

uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsAlarmClea.name: uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsAlarmCleared
uxAlmMaximumNumberofSIPSessionsAlarmClea.description: SIP sessions per signaling group is under the maximum limit

uxAlmErrorresolvingSRVrecord.name: uxAlmErrorresolvingSRVrecord
uxAlmErrorresolvingSRVrecord.description: Failed to execute SRV record query. Suggested action - confirm that DNS server network is reachable, check SRV and DNS server configuration.

uxAlmSRVrecordresolved.name: uxAlmSRVrecordresolved
uxAlmSRVrecordresolved.description: DNS server returned valid SRV record(s).

uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartFail.name: uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartFailure
uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartFail.description: Handshake failed due to start with invalid certificate. Action: Import a valid signed Sonus SBC Certificate on local and/or remote gateway.

uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartSucc.name: uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartSuccessful
uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeNegotiationStartSucc.description: Handshake response was started with valid certificate on local and remote gateway. This event clears the 'SIP-TLS Handshake Negotiation Start Failure' alarm.

uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGsreached.name: uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGsreached
uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGsreached.description: SIP signaling group Count Reached maximum Supported Limit.

uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGscleared.name: uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGscleared
uxAlmMaximumsupportedSIPSGscleared.description: SIP signaling group Count is under the maximum Supported

uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionsreached.name: uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionsreached
uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionsreached.description: Number of SIP Non Call Sessions is over the system capacity

uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionscleared.name: uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionscleared
uxAlmMaximumnonSIPCallSessionscleared.description: Number of SIP Non Call Sessions is under the system capacity

uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionsreached.name: uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionsreached
uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionsreached.description: Number of SIP Call Sessions is over the system capacity

uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionscleared.name: uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionscleared
uxAlmMaximumSIPCallSessionscleared.description: Number of SIP Call Sessions is under the system capacity

uxAlmSIPSGListenProtocolandSIPServerHost.name: uxAlmSIPSGListenProtocolandSIPServerHostProtocolmismatch
uxAlmSIPSGListenProtocolandSIPServerHost.description: Verify that the Listen Ports and Protocols for the SG match those in the Server Table

uxAlmConfigurationErrorSIPSGandServerPro.name: uxAlmConfigurationErrorSIPSGandServerProtocolMismatch
uxAlmConfigurationErrorSIPSGandServerPro.description: Verify that the Listen Ports and Protocols for the SG match those in the Server Table

uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailure.name: uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailure
uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailure.description: TLS client handshake failed with alert code. Action: Refer to Error Alerts in RFC 5246 for the problem.

uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutCle.name: uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutCleared
uxAlmSIPTLSHandshakeInactivityTimeoutCle.description: Handshake response was received within specified timeout. This event clears the 'SIP-TLS Handshake Inactivity Timeout Failure' alarm.

uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailureCleared.name: uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailureCleared
uxAlmSIPTLSServerHandshakeFailureCleared.description: Handshake failure error alert condition was cleared. This event clears the 'SIP-TLS Server Handshake Failure' alarm.

uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailureCleared.name: uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailureCleared
uxAlmSIPTLSClientHandshakeFailureCleared.description: Handshake failure error alert condition was cleared. This event clears the 'SIP-TLS Client Handshake Failure' alarm.

uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFail.name: uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFailure
uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFail.description: A Presence Publish Request has been sent to the configured Lync Presence Front End and has received no response or a failed response.

uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFail.name: uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFailureCleared
uxAlmSkypeLyncPresenceServerResponseFail.description: A presence server that previously was unreachable has successfully sent a message that the SBC has received.

uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIP.name: uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIP
uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIP.description: An INVITE message was received from a host without a matching Federated IP

uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIPCleared.name: uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIPCleared
uxAlmSIPRequestfromUntrustedIPCleared.description: Source IP is added to the list of federated IP Addresses.

uxAlmReSyncmessagereceivedonSGnotselecte.name: uxAlmReSyncmessagereceivedonSGnotselectedforAutoConfigtask
uxAlmReSyncmessagereceivedonSGnotselecte.description: Check Auto Configuration Task settings and verify that the Signalling Group selected is correct.

uxAlmMaximumNumberofSkypeLyncPresenceSes.name: uxAlmMaximumNumberofSkypeLyncPresenceSessionsReached
uxAlmMaximumNumberofSkypeLyncPresenceSes.description: The maximum number of 500 concurrent SIP Publish sessions for Presence has been reached. Skype/Lync Presence processing will be suspended until the number of concurrent sessions drops below 500 limit.

uxAlmMaximumNumberofS4BPresencePublishSe.name: uxAlmMaximumNumberofS4BPresencePublishSessionsAlarmCleared
uxAlmMaximumNumberofS4BPresencePublishSe.description: SIP Publish sessions for S4B Presence is under the maximum limit

uxAlmEnableMonitoringonSkypePresenceServ.name: uxAlmEnableMonitoringonSkypePresenceServerforbetterreliability
uxAlmEnableMonitoringonSkypePresenceServ.description: Enable Monitoring on Skype Presence Server for better reliability.

uxAlmMonitoringonSkypePresenceServerhasb.name: uxAlmMonitoringonSkypePresenceServerhasbeenenabled
uxAlmMonitoringonSkypePresenceServerhasb.description: Monitoring on Skype Presence Server has been enabled.

uxAlmDChanneldown.name: uxAlmDChanneldown
uxAlmDChanneldown.description: The D-channel(layer 2) is out of service.

uxAlmCallreleasedduetochannelrestartbyfa.name: uxAlmCallreleasedduetochannelrestartbyfarend
uxAlmCallreleasedduetochannelrestartbyfa.description: Call released as the ISDN channel has been restarted by far end.

uxAlmPortdisabledbyoperator.name: uxAlmPortdisabledbyoperator
uxAlmPortdisabledbyoperator.description: Port is placed Out of Service by operator.

uxAlmPortenabledbyoperator.name: uxAlmPortenabledbyoperator
uxAlmPortenabledbyoperator.description: Port is placed back in Service by operator.

uxAlmDS1LoopbackEnter.name: uxAlmDS1LoopbackEnter
uxAlmDS1LoopbackEnter.description: The physical layer is in loopback state.

uxAlmDS1LoopbackExit.name: uxAlmDS1LoopbackExit
uxAlmDS1LoopbackExit.description: The physical layer is out of loopback state.

uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignal.name: uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignal
uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignal.description: The physical layer has detected a RED (LOS) alarm.

uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignalcleared.name: uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignalcleared
uxAlmRedAlarmLossofSignalcleared.description: The physical layer RED alarm (LOS) is cleared.
